<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Wearing a symbiote that is invisible (i.e. rotting Q) turns character invisible but doesn't register in character report. Also logically only the symbiote part would be invisible, character would remain visible. <p>
<a href="./amaurea">amaurea</a>: I thought the sybiosis intermingled cells between the two parts, letting them share some of their powers. I don't think it is a bug that a Q gives invisibility to the player. The char sheet part is irritating, though, and occurs not only here, but for gods too. This will be fixed in tome3, I think. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Fixed this in ToME 2.3.0. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>:  Thanks for this too (I assume it's very related to the god advantages etc.. 
</p>
